# DataVex Growth Intelligence Engine — Build Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A production-grade multi-agent AI content pipeline — end-to-end — from a single keyword input to publish-ready blog, LinkedIn, and Twitter content with quality scoring.

---

## Backend (FastAPI + LangGraph)

### File Structure
```
backend/
├── main.py                 # FastAPI app: /health, /run-pipeline (SSE), /run-pipeline-sync
├── config.py               # Pydantic settings loading .env
├── models.py               # Full Pydantic model hierarchy for all I/O
├── agents/                 # 10 AI agents (all using claude-sonnet-4-6)
│   ├── base.py             # Shared Claude client + brand system prompt
│   ├── signal_discovery.py # Tavily search → top 5 signals
│   ├── signal_scorer.py    # 4-dim confidence scoring (authority/recency/relevance/novelty)
│   ├── signal_validator.py # URL reachability + Claude fact extraction
│   ├── serp_scanner.py     # Tavily SERP → competitor angles + content gaps
│   ├── strategy_brief.py   # Editorial brief with rejected angles + rationale
│   ├── blog_generator.py   # 800-1200w SEO blog post generation
│   ├── blog_critique.py    # 6-dimension critique (hook/clarity/authority/differentiation/structure/brand)
│   ├── short_form_generator.py  # LinkedIn (200-300w) + Twitter thread (6-8 tweets)
│   └── short_form_critique.py  # 5-dimension critique (hook/platform/engagement/share/brand)
└── pipeline/
    ├── graph.py            # LangGraph StateGraph: 16 nodes, linear flow
    ├── state.py            # TypedDict pipeline state schema
    ├── quality_gate.py     # 7/10 threshold gate, max 3 iterations
    └── output_assembler.py # Assembles final PipelineOutput JSON
```

### Pipeline Flow (16 LangGraph nodes)
```
discover_signals → score_signals → validate_signal → scan_serp
→ strategy_brief
→ generate_blog_draft1 → critique_blog_1 → generate_blog_draft2 → critique_blog_2 → blog_quality_gate
→ generate_short_form_draft1 → critique_short_form_1 → generate_short_form_draft2 → critique_short_form_2 → short_form_quality_gate
→ assemble_output
```

